======================================================================
G8 — Display Curated Paper Figures
======================================================================
Methodological note: this step displays curated TeX-facing figures only.
## fig:appendix_cox_ph_diagnostics
Comparable Cox proportional-hazards diagnostic for the covariates showing the strongest evidence of possible non-proportionality. The overall pattern is consistent with the notebook's C\_broad\_departure classification; the comparable Cox anchor should therefore be treated as an approximate benchmark specification.
Image(filename='/Users/rafars/rafael.dasilva@eastern.edu - Google Drive/My Drive/DOUTORADO/Eastern/dropout_test-1/outputs_benchmark_survival/paper_appendix/fig_appendix_cox_ph_diagnostics.png')
- /Users/rafars/rafael.dasilva@eastern.edu - Google Drive/My Drive/DOUTORADO/Eastern/dropout_test-1/outputs_benchmark_survival/paper_appendix/fig_appendix_cox_ph_diagnostics.png
## fig:ablation_impact
Ablation impact across tuned model families, contrasting the loss associated with removing static versus temporal-behavioral signal. Across all families, removing temporal-behavioral signal is more damaging than removing static covariates.
Image(filename='/Users/rafars/rafael.dasilva@eastern.edu - Google Drive/My Drive/DOUTORADO/Eastern/dropout_test-1/outputs_benchmark_survival/paper_main/fig_paper_02_ablation_impact.png')
- /Users/rafars/rafael.dasilva@eastern.edu - Google Drive/My Drive/DOUTORADO/Eastern/dropout_test-1/outputs_benchmark_survival/paper_main/fig_paper_02_ablation_impact.png
## fig:benchmark_tuned_comparison
Benchmark comparison of all 14 tuned model families under the harmonized survival-oriented protocol, grouped by arm. Within the comparable arm, RSF leads on time-dependent concordance and Brier horizons; XGBoost AFT is a visible outlier. Within the dynamic arm, all five families cluster tightly on IBS.
Image(filename='/Users/rafars/rafael.dasilva@eastern.edu - Google Drive/My Drive/DOUTORADO/Eastern/dropout_test-1/outputs_benchmark_survival/paper_main/fig_paper_01_benchmark_family_expanded_comparison.png')
- /Users/rafars/rafael.dasilva@eastern.edu - Google Drive/My Drive/DOUTORADO/Eastern/dropout_test-1/outputs_benchmark_survival/paper_main/fig_paper_01_benchmark_family_expanded_comparison.png
## fig:explainability_block_dominance
Normalized explainability block dominance for the comparable-arm tuned families in the manuscript-facing export. Values are normalized within model to highlight relative block importance; the figure should be read as a within-model comparison of dominant signal blocks, not as an absolute cross-model magnitude comparison.
Image(filename='/Users/rafars/rafael.dasilva@eastern.edu - Google Drive/My Drive/DOUTORADO/Eastern/dropout_test-1/outputs_benchmark_survival/paper_main/fig_paper_03_explainability_block_dominance_normalized.png')
